UML:TaggedValue.value: 1. The Research Investigator indicates that he will define a new query. 2. The system presents an interface to define the query specific to the type of entity in question. See the various associated Special Requirements.

3. The Research Investigator defines the query criteria (default no criteria, returning all entries). The system allows the Research Investigator to add a single criterion at a time providing all the operators (=, >, <, wildcard match, etc.) appropriate to the field and the specified criterion value. By default all criteria are "anded" together. All clinical and imaging feature data fields may be used as criteria. 4. The Research Investigator chooses the fields to be displayed in the result set. 5. The Research Investigator defines the ordering of the result set.
6. The Research Investigator saves the query, giving it a unique name and a description.
6. The Research Investigator executes the query.

QueryForm is intended to provide a more UI oriented view of the Query for getting and setting Query configuration. The example operations setName and setDescription would be simple passthroughs (and might be removed in favor of directly accessing the underlying Query object). Operations supporting setting query criteria, grouping ANDs and ORs are more challenging and will required this mediating view.
Translates any changes to the QueryForm to the underlying Query. Additional validation may occur here as well.
Calls the various findX methods to find entities that match Query critiera.
Both actions are Session scope to allow query definition and results to persist between requests.
